-- Foreign Direct Investment in Pakistan Falls 40.7% in Year Ended June 30
-- Farhan Sharif
-- 2010-07-14T12:18:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/foreign-direct-investment-in-pakistan-falls-40-7-in-year-ended-june-30.html

          
          
             Foreign direct investment in
Pakistan fell 40.7 percent to $2.2 billion in the year ended
June 30, according to an e-mailed statement from the central
bank.  
